<p>The <code>date</code> function formats a timestamp using PHP date format.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}$sampleTimestamp | date('Y-m-d'){close}</pre>
<p>Formatted: <b>{$sampleTimestamp | date('Y-m-d')}</b></p>

<h2>Common Formats</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('Y-m-d'){close}</pre>
<p>ISO date: <b>{now | date('Y-m-d')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('d/m/Y'){close}</pre>
<p>European: <b>{now | date('d/m/Y')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('m/d/Y'){close}</pre>
<p>US format: <b>{now | date('m/d/Y')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('F j, Y'){close}</pre>
<p>Long format: <b>{now | date('F j, Y')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('D, M j'){close}</pre>
<p>Short format: <b>{now | date('D, M j')}</b></p>

<h2>Time Formats</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('H:i:s'){close}</pre>
<p>24-hour time: <b>{now | date('H:i:s')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('g:i A'){close}</pre>
<p>12-hour time: <b>{now | date('g:i A')}</b></p>

<h2>With Modifier</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('Y-m-d', '+1 week'){close}</pre>
<p>Next week: <b>{now | date('Y-m-d', '+1 week')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('Y-m-d', '-1 month'){close}</pre>
<p>Last month: <b>{now | date('Y-m-d', '-1 month')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}now | date('F Y', '+6 months'){close}</pre>
<p>In 6 months: <b>{now | date('F Y', '+6 months')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Example</h2>
<pre>{open}now | date('Y') | + 0{close} &copy;</pre>
<p>Copyright: <b>{now | date('Y') | + 0} &copy;</b></p>
